Subject: Re: [VB] Electrical help needed no start. ground?


If you don't have a tranny ground strap, you've no real way of grounding
your starter for the high starter current. There are other small paths to
ground from the engine, but none can carry the starter current. 

Get that ground strap on there!

cal, leaving NY tomorrow for FL!!!
67 deluxe


